==English==
===Etymology===
Adverb form of [[apparent]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈpɛɹ.ɛnt.li/

===Adverb===
# [[plainly|Plainly]]; [[clearly]]; [[manifestly]]; [[evidently]].
#:    If he should scorn me so apparently. --Shak.
# [[seemingly|Seemingly]]; [[in appearance]]; as, a man may be apparently friendly, yet malicious in heart.
